[19]The Deesis continues to appear in Western art, but not as often or in such an invariable composition as in the East.
[20]In the West the image showed a full-length enthroned Christ, often in a mandorla or other geometrical frame, surrounded by the symbols of the Four Evangelists, representing the vision of Chapters 4 and 5 of the Book of Revelation.
